From 5f69c76dfb20c23aa154340354d199684e30e524 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Meng Li <Meng.Li@windriver.com>
Date: Mon, 9 Feb 2026 16:04:51 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 18/30] drivers: drm: use video aperture helpers explicitly

Based on kernel upstream commit 689274a56c0c("drm: Remove
DRM aperture helpers"), it needs to use video aperture helpers
explicitly.

Upstream-Status: Pending

Signed-off-by: Meng Li <Meng.Li@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/tegra/drm.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/tegra/drm.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/tegra/drm.c
index 23d387d9..4bbea220 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/tegra/drm.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/tegra/drm.c
@@ -1332,6 +1332,7 @@ static int host1x_drm_probe(struct host1x_device *dev)
 #else
 		err = drm_aperture_remove_framebuffers(false, "tegradrmfb");
 #endif
+
 		if (err < 0)
 			goto hub;
 	}
-- 
2.34.1

